<subSubSection id="538FDCB3FFE1FF8EFF0203ADFCD852C9" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF0203ADFE8353D8" blockId="4.[212,1172,647,774]" box="[212,344,647,671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading id="40623854FFE1FF8EFF0203ADFE8353D8" box="[212,344,647,671]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFE1FF8EFF0203ADFE8353D8" box="[212,344,647,671]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF020384FBC35241" blockId="4.[212,1172,647,774]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Native to America, Amazon Basin (
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFE1FF8EFDBD0384FD695381" box="[619,690,686,710]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFE1FF8EFD6B0385FD2F5381" box="[701,756,687,710]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFE1FF8EFCD60384FC895381" box="[768,850,686,710]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFE1FF8EFCBE0384FB5F5381" author="Cowie RH &amp; Thiengo SC" box="[872,1156,686,710]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="41 - 100" refId="ref9716" refString="Cowie RH, Thiengo SC. 2003. The apple snails of the Americas (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Asolene, Felipponea, Marisa, Pomacea, Pomella): a nomenclatural and type catalog. Malacologia. 45: 41 - 100." type="journal article" year="2003">Cowie and Thiengo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFE1FF8EFF2103E4FEED53A1" box="[247,310,718,742]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Chile</collectingCountry>
, this species was found for the first time in the country in 2000 (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFE1FF8EFBEB03E4FE915241" author="Letelier S &amp; Ramos AM &amp; Huaquin L" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="9 - 13" refId="ref11852" refString="Letelier S, Ramos AM, Huaquin L. 2007. Moluscos dulceacuicolas exoticos en Chile. Rev Mex Biodivers. 78: 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="2007">Letelier et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and has been recorded only in Santiago (
<geoCoordinate id="7EA1E9FFFFE1FF8EFCE703C4FC4B5241" box="[817,912,750,774]" degrees="33" direction="south" minutes="27" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" precision="925" value="-33.45">
33°27 
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFE1FF8EFCA403C4FCA35241" bold="true" box="[882,888,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="7EA1E9FFFFE1FF8EFC4903C4FBD05241" box="[927,1035,750,774]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="38" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" precision="925" value="-70.63333">
70°38 
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFE1FF8EFC0803C4FC3F5241" bold="true" box="[990,996,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF020264FD715221" blockId="4.[212,771,846,910]" box="[212,682,846,870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading id="40623854FFE1FF8EFF020264FD715221" box="[212,682,846,870]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFE1FF8EFF020264FD715221" box="[212,682,846,870]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Possible mechanism of introduction/Status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF02025CFCD852C9" blockId="4.[212,771,846,910]" box="[212,771,886,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Aquarium trade/established (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFE1FF8EFDCB025CFD2852C9" author="Letelier S &amp; Ramos AM &amp; Huaquin L" box="[541,755,886,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="9 - 13" refId="ref11852" refString="Letelier S, Ramos AM, Huaquin L. 2007. Moluscos dulceacuicolas exoticos en Chile. Rev Mex Biodivers. 78: 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="2007">Letelier et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="538FDCB3FFE1FF8EFF0202FCFE705572" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF0202FCFEED52A9" blockId="4.[212,1171,982,1077]" box="[212,310,982,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
<heading id="40623854FFE1FF8EFF0202FCFEED52A9" box="[212,310,982,1006]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFE1FF8EFF0202FCFEED52A9" box="[212,310,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFE1FF8EFF0202D7FE705572" blockId="4.[212,1171,982,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735">
Polyphagous, invasive, they can compete with native freshwater species (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFE1FF8EFBC402D7FE915572" author="Aditya G &amp; Raut SK" pageId="4" pageNumber="1735" pagination="919 - 921" refId="ref8528" refString="Aditya G, Raut SK. 2001. Food of the snail, Pomacea bridgesii, introduced in India. Curr Sci. 80: 919 - 921." type="journal article" year="2001">Aditya and Raut 2001</bibRefCitation>
). EA, I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
